The department will launch an e-ticket system in the taxi industry which will see a cashless payment. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Transport MEC Ismail Vadi says the department will launch an e-ticket system in the taxi industry which will see a cashless payment method. Today is the launch of the provincial October Transport Month Campaign under the theme Modernisation of the Public Transport System in Gauteng. Vadi says the department has cracked down on the taxi industry this year and there have been improvements. "We'll be launching the concept of an e-ticket for the taxi industry. In fact, I think the date is 17 October and it will be done in Tshwane. "The pilot study had been done and the testing has been done and I think we can begin to launch the concept. We're moving toward the cashless system of running the taxi industry."